  "prompt": "How much of Google's mobile revenue comes from apps versus mobile search in browsers and the mobile web?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, specific figures detailing the exact percentage of Google's mobile revenue that comes from apps versus mobile search in browsers and the mobile web are not publicly available. Google generates a significant portion of its revenue from mobile advertising, which includes both app ads and web search ads, but it does not typically break these down into exact percentages.\n\nGenerally, app monetization through platforms like Google Play and in-app advertising contributes substantially to Google's revenue, alongside its extensive search advertising network, which optimizes for mobile usage as well. \n\nFor the most specific and current figures, I recommend checking the latest financial reports from Google\u2019s parent company, Alphabet Inc., or industry analysis from reputable market research firms.",
